WEBVTT

00:14.306 --> 00:14.747
Good morning.

00:16.770 --> 00:17.751
It's good to be with all of you.

00:19.674 --> 00:23.821
Indeed, as you've already heard, we're starting a new year.

00:24.361 --> 00:27.266
And with a new year, we always start with some kind of theme.

00:27.907 --> 00:30.591
And this year, we are transformed.

00:32.013 --> 00:36.360
I think this theme is found throughout our scriptures.

00:37.021 --> 00:42.930
I think this is the desire of God's heart for each and every one of you and for me as well.

00:44.002 --> 00:47.588
This isn't to say this has happened in fullness.

00:48.449 --> 00:52.576
I don't yet proclaim that I'm that butterfly and nor are you.

00:53.377 --> 00:55.240
But that is certainly the goal, right?

00:55.260 --> 01:05.938
And we've got to have somewhere that we're aiming at if we're going to get from the smallest little part here to the eventual butterfly on the other side.

01:06.370 --> 01:26.964
Our scriptures talk about it actually with great regularity, especially once you hit the New Testament, but even the Old Testament has these promises and expectations that as we meet God face to face, and as we come into contact with Jesus, we will be transformed.

01:27.805 --> 01:33.234
I wanna read for you just a few of these, starting with Ezekiel, the Old Testament one.

01:33.794 --> 01:41.483
36, 26 to 27, says, I will give you a new heart and put a new spirit in you.

01:41.503 --> 01:48.652
I will remove from your heart the heart of stone and I will give you a fresh, a heart of flesh.

01:49.453 --> 01:53.277
And I will put my spirit in you and move you to follow my decrees.

01:54.839 --> 01:57.202
And that's one of the big promises of the Old Testament.

01:57.282 --> 02:10.978
that with the coming of Jesus, with the Messiah, there is an opportunity for the indwelling of the Holy Spirit that literally changes us, as we just sang, from the inside out, that we will actually have new hearts.

02:11.799 --> 02:13.601
Not hearts of stone, but hearts of flesh.

02:15.163 --> 02:21.891
And then when we get to our New Testament, we see this is exactly what our writers and what Jesus himself is teaching us.

02:22.151 --> 02:24.434
And so for example, in 2 Corinthians 5,

02:24.994 --> 02:28.679
Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation.

02:28.739 --> 02:30.621
The old has passed away.

02:30.681 --> 02:32.163
Behold, the new has come."

02:32.784 --> 02:44.899
Or 2 Corinthians 3, we all with unveiled face, beholding the glory of the Lord, are being transformed into the same image from one degree of glory to another.

02:45.600 --> 02:47.783
For this comes from the Lord who is the spirit.

02:48.884 --> 02:53.490
Or Ephesians 4, put off your old self.

02:53.890 --> 03:17.172
be renewed in the spirit of your minds, put on the new self, created after the likeness of God in true righteousness and holiness, or finally in Philippians 1, being confident of this, that he who began a good work in you will carry it on to completion until the day of Christ Jesus.

03:19.835 --> 03:22.898
The Christian life is not an easy one.

03:23.234 --> 03:27.179
but it is supposed to be an upward trajectory.

03:28.200 --> 03:33.126
It is one of transformation, it is one of growth and even discovery.

03:36.771 --> 03:46.443
We'll confess to you however, there is, as you probably look around in the church, maybe not our church, the church outside these walls.

03:47.424 --> 03:51.890
We notice that there are people who maybe need some more transformation.

03:52.162 --> 03:53.484
among our ranks.

03:54.845 --> 04:02.414
And you might think to yourself, well, boy, if the New Testament is promising all of this transformation, what is going on?

04:03.535 --> 04:05.057
And what has happened to these people?

04:06.619 --> 04:14.889
And then if we're brutally honest, we look inward and we think, well, maybe I've got a little work left to do on myself.

04:16.210 --> 04:19.474
And there's some transformation that still needs to happen right here.

04:21.282 --> 04:25.727
Here's my desperate hope for South from Baptist Church in 2026.

04:25.868 --> 04:37.542
Is that we be a people who are on a path together, supporting one another, locking arms together, encouraging one another on this path of transformation.

04:38.323 --> 04:42.068
Not because we've arrived, but because we need to walk it together.

04:44.250 --> 04:45.091
Let's start with some prayer.

04:46.853 --> 04:50.578
Heavenly Father, God, as we begin this year together,

04:52.098 --> 04:52.919
We start with prayer.

04:53.960 --> 04:54.661
We start with you.

04:57.485 --> 04:58.426
We need your grace.

05:01.289 --> 05:02.070
We need your power.

05:03.892 --> 05:04.893
We need your forgiveness.

05:07.897 --> 05:16.668
And so God, if we are going to put the past behind us, if we're going to put that old self behind us, we need your power.

05:17.889 --> 05:18.610
We need you now.

05:20.514 --> 05:38.151
Jesus, we give you thanks for the cross, upon which you nailed to it all of our pasts, all of those sins and those things that have brought us down, the pain, the hurt, and the ways that we have hurt others.

05:40.414 --> 05:42.255
Jesus, we give you thanks for the cross.

05:44.277 --> 05:46.139
But we know that the cross was not the end.

05:47.941 --> 05:48.882
Resurrection is.

05:50.114 --> 05:55.661
And so Jesus, we give you thanks for resurrection and the possibility of new life.

05:58.484 --> 06:02.569
Got here and now, we entrust ourselves to that new life.

06:04.612 --> 06:19.730
We say we believe that new life is possible in each and every one of us, that through the power of your cross, that each of us can live new creation lives.

06:20.610 --> 06:24.034
metamorphosized lives, transformed lives.

06:25.156 --> 06:26.497
We pray this in Christ's name, amen.

06:29.341 --> 06:37.871
My friend, Mike, one of my few friends from high school that I occasionally keep in touch with, he lives in Virginia.

06:37.891 --> 06:49.586
He came from a very difficult home and never married and he lives alone to this day and now he runs a rescue out of his home.

06:49.794 --> 06:50.895
a rescue for animals.

06:51.997 --> 06:57.984
And one can imagine that he receives lots of abused animals.

06:58.244 --> 07:06.334
And so take for an example, he receives an abused dog, right?

07:06.354 --> 07:11.781
And that abused dog when he goes to feed it, cowers in fear.

07:12.923 --> 07:18.930
That abused dog, despite Mike's loving presence and the safety

07:19.330 --> 07:25.601
of Mike's home and the safety of the rescue that he's created, that dog will still do what?

07:25.841 --> 07:45.554
It will still act out of fear and it still has that abuse sitting somewhere in his head or in his background and so despite all of the promises and the opportunity that is there for the dog until it is trained and transformed into this

07:45.858 --> 07:53.768
new, loving, safe home that it finds itself in, it will still act out of its old nature.

07:55.470 --> 07:59.855
I think this is part and parcel of what it means to live the Christian life.

08:00.636 --> 08:14.674
There is this old way that has been ingrained in our minds, and that with Jesus Christ and the acceptance of salvation, a way has been made into a very safe and loving arms of a father.

08:17.122 --> 08:25.430
But I think most of us, sometimes we still act out of those old ways of being.

08:26.371 --> 08:36.562
And despite the safety and the love and the adoption that the Father offers to us, sometimes we still act out of fear.

08:37.443 --> 08:41.887
Sometimes we still act out of old ways of living.

08:43.188 --> 08:44.690
The transformed life

08:45.218 --> 09:12.274
is coming to realization that those old ways need to be old and gone and done, and that we need to live in a way that embraces the loving gaze of the Father who looks at us and says, you are safe, you are loved, you are mine, and I am transforming you into the image of God that you were created to be.

09:14.370 --> 09:19.097
When I read Romans 12, one and two, this is what I find.

09:19.597 --> 09:22.722
If you'll turn there with me, I'll show you what I mean.

09:25.326 --> 09:29.692
Romans 12 sits at the hinge of the entire book of Romans.

09:29.772 --> 09:35.340
Many of you know Romans to be Paul's magnum opus, the best thing he's written, and it is true.

09:35.861 --> 09:42.290
The theology of chapters one to 11, which is what it is, it's like this grand work of theology,

09:42.498 --> 09:45.143
is unlike anything else he writes.

09:46.005 --> 09:55.063
But as Paul often does in his letters, he has this first part that is theology, and then he bridges into a part that is very practical.

09:55.865 --> 09:57.849
And we are sitting at that hinge right there.

09:57.889 --> 10:04.242
The 12 and through 16 is the practical part of his letter.

10:04.994 --> 10:17.288
And so when we get to this one word in chapter 12, it says, I appeal to you therefore, therefore is doing a whole lot of heavy lifting in this sentence.

10:17.668 --> 10:24.216
It's three Greek letters, but it's doing a whole lot of lifting because it is the hinge on which all of this book sits.

10:25.437 --> 10:33.586
And Paul is saying this, I am appealing to you, therefore, my brothers and sisters, by the mercies of God.

10:34.242 --> 10:41.051
The mercies of God, what he's saying here, is a reference to everything that he has said from one to 11.

10:41.932 --> 10:45.197
And if I can just sum it up very briefly for you, it goes like this.

10:46.158 --> 10:46.999
God loves you.

10:48.581 --> 10:50.764
He sent his son Jesus to die for you.

10:51.625 --> 10:55.671
While we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

10:56.732 --> 10:59.216
He wants to adopt us into his family.

10:59.776 --> 11:01.899
He wants to save us and to redeem us.

11:02.780 --> 11:03.922
And he wants to

11:04.418 --> 11:05.419
transform us.

11:06.200 --> 11:09.084
He is a God of love and a God of mercy.

11:10.085 --> 11:27.806
And because of all those things, therefore, I implore you, brothers and sisters, by those mercies that I just talked about for 11 chapters, you should present yourself as a living sacrifice.

11:29.147 --> 11:31.410
Because of chapters 1 through 11,

11:31.714 --> 11:36.420
You should live a different kind of life is what Paul is saying here.

11:36.440 --> 11:42.809
The living sacrifice is a phrase I quite like.

11:44.091 --> 11:46.254
It is a contradiction in terms.

11:46.715 --> 11:50.840
A sacrifice is something that is typically dead, right?

11:51.020 --> 11:52.382
It has been slaughtered.

11:52.823 --> 11:57.970
Certainly in the ancient world, this was true when animal sacrifice was still being practiced.

11:58.626 --> 12:02.090
And so to have a living sacrifice, well, what in the world might that mean?

12:02.851 --> 12:09.039
Let me suggest to you, it means somebody who is living a life in submission to God.

12:09.559 --> 12:28.242
They have given their whole life over day after day after day to the God who is being appealed to in one through 11, described in one through 11 as this God who loves you so much that he sent Jesus Christ to die on our behalf that we might live.

12:30.818 --> 12:49.802
And so we are to present our lives in a living sacrifice kind of way, day after day, submitting our wills to the will of God because we believe that His will is better than is more full than whatever it is that we might bring to the table.

12:50.803 --> 12:59.474
And so we are to present ourselves as a living sacrifice and this sacrifice when done right and from the heart

13:00.130 --> 13:01.632
is a holy sacrifice.

13:01.692 --> 13:04.615
It is set apart, and it is acceptable to God.

13:05.116 --> 13:10.441
And this is our, as Paul says, our spiritual worship.

13:12.264 --> 13:13.725
At least that's what the ESV says.

13:15.127 --> 13:18.551
It's not my favorite translation of this, where it's actually a very odd one.

13:18.571 --> 13:25.298
Some of you, if you've got your Bibles open, you might have something different where it says spiritual worship.

13:25.378 --> 13:30.564
Can anyone shout out if there's especially the word spiritual here?

13:31.565 --> 13:33.267
Does someone have a different word sitting there?

13:34.288 --> 13:36.791
Like truth, yeah, reasonable.

13:38.072 --> 13:52.228
This word spiritual is our word logic actually, which is interesting to me because it's something more rational or again truthful or it's something real.

13:52.348 --> 13:53.810
It's like the really real.

13:54.402 --> 14:00.649
And then the worship, it's not the hands in the air, but like we were just singing together, it's not that kind of worship.

14:00.969 --> 14:12.060
It's again, it's the sacrifice imagery of the priest who is slaughtering the animal and bringing that act of worship by serving the community.

14:12.621 --> 14:16.845
And so it's this real kind of living, it's this real kind of serving.

14:16.885 --> 14:21.330
And if I could just sum up 12-1 for us, it would be this.

14:23.074 --> 14:44.696
in your day-to-day, Monday kind of life, everything we do, minute by minute, is meant to be offered up as a submission to God's will because of what he has done for us by adopting us into the household of God.

14:47.379 --> 14:50.322
And so again, back to the dog analogy.

14:50.978 --> 15:04.392
The sadness of that dog is that he can't walk into the new master's house and live in the freedom and the abundance that he should because there is freedom and abundance there.

15:04.432 --> 15:11.439
And there is a sense of safety and love that is waiting if you just open your eyes to see it.

15:12.460 --> 15:18.546
But over time, as you become accustomed to the ways of the master,

15:19.106 --> 15:28.701
You should be able to look into the Master's eyes and see it is safe, it is good, and I am to be transformed into the very nature of this Master.

15:29.823 --> 15:39.198
That God Himself is trying to transform me into the image of God that we were created in back in Genesis chapter 1.

15:40.480 --> 15:41.682
And so therefore,

15:42.338 --> 15:52.091
by these mercies, by being brought into this household, we are to present our very lives as God's image bearers in the world.

15:53.533 --> 16:04.569
And then it gets to the second verse, which is indeed the verse that will probably guide us for at least a few months, if not hopefully the whole year.

16:04.609 --> 16:08.594
And it's this, do not be conformed

16:08.706 --> 16:13.333
to the world that is around us, but be transformed by the renewing of our minds.

16:15.276 --> 16:19.603
Let's start with the first half.

16:19.623 --> 16:27.736
I once heard a joke that a fish swims up to another fish and says, how's the water?

16:28.397 --> 16:31.041
And the other fish says, what's water?

16:33.605 --> 16:34.467
And the idea is this.

16:35.649 --> 16:36.530
The idea is that

16:37.378 --> 16:44.588
That fish just knows what the surroundings are and knows not to give it a name, water.

16:45.189 --> 16:48.934
It is, for them, the air he breathes, so to speak.

16:50.056 --> 16:58.247
And for you and me, the world, well, the world is just the way things are, at least the way we assume them to be.

16:58.287 --> 17:06.258
And we are not to be conformed to the way that we think things are just supposed to be.

17:07.394 --> 17:10.158
And this looks like a lot of different things, doesn't it?

17:10.519 --> 17:16.327
Sometimes it's what we might think of as like the hot sins of sex and murder and stealing and the like.

17:17.609 --> 17:28.706
But often it's simpler or maybe more complex or secret things like we live in a world of anxiety that we shouldn't be living in or we just embrace it as it is.

17:29.908 --> 17:36.658
Or we live in a world of moral outrage, but we're always outraged at the wrong things it seems.

17:37.442 --> 17:54.269
or we live in the world of consumerism where we just take it at face value that we too are to be these consumers and that we are supposed to just receive constantly rather than actually pour our lives out for other people around us.

17:56.132 --> 18:04.786
Or the world is tribalism and we just assume that's the water we swim in and so we are supposed to swim in that.

18:06.082 --> 18:20.325
Paul reminds us we are not to be conformed by the ways of the world, that we are supposed to name water as water, or the world as the world, and to not give in to those kinds of ways.

18:22.609 --> 18:26.034
So my hope is that every Sunday morning,

18:26.274 --> 18:30.759
You come, you gather together, we gather together, we sing songs of praise.

18:31.060 --> 18:34.464
We remind ourselves of who God is and who we are in Christ.

18:35.185 --> 18:40.191
You hear a message from me that might last 30 minutes, maybe a little longer sometimes.

18:40.792 --> 18:45.898
And then we go out into the world, battle ready for what the world is gonna throw at us.

18:48.461 --> 18:55.890
But if that really is the only model, then I worry for us because I get about 30 minutes of your time.

18:56.450 --> 18:58.252
but the world gets the rest of the time.

18:59.113 --> 19:13.731
And so whatever you're listening to on your podcasts, or you're watching on your televisions, or shows up on your social media screens, whether you realize it or not, that is training you to think in some kind of way.

19:14.311 --> 19:19.698
And you need to say to yourself, is this, is this the world speaking to me?

19:21.880 --> 19:23.282
Or is this the voice of God?

19:26.690 --> 19:34.439
do not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewal of your mind.

19:37.502 --> 19:45.271
Conforming to the world looks a little bit like a sled track.

19:45.791 --> 19:52.058
You know when you go sledding, right, and there's snow on the ground in winter instead of whatever's happening right now.

19:53.460 --> 19:55.442
And you go down the track,

19:56.034 --> 19:58.478
And then it starts to create a groove, right?

19:58.838 --> 20:04.247
And you get enough people going down the groove, then it just automatically takes you where you're supposed to go.

20:04.287 --> 20:08.454
That is conformity, right?

20:08.474 --> 20:11.959
Now being transformed is the opposite of that.

20:12.100 --> 20:23.698
Like where you are going down this track, to be transformed is difficult because it means like hopping the track and then starting a new kind of groove.

20:24.194 --> 20:33.467
And that can be very, very awkward and difficult, hard, scary, indeed, right?

20:34.168 --> 20:37.313
And yet this is precisely what Paul is calling us to.

20:37.373 --> 20:46.886
This is what our scriptures are calling us to, to jump out of the groove that is created by the sleds and to begin to be transformed in different ways.

20:49.069 --> 20:52.434
This is the slightest bit of brain science for us this morning.

20:52.514 --> 20:54.957
A brain too has these grooves, right?

20:55.798 --> 20:56.338
Do you know this?

20:57.099 --> 21:07.851
And like literal physical grooves that as you repeat actions over time and as you do things over time, those grooves get deeper and deeper and deeper.

21:07.911 --> 21:18.143
And then in order to not do that action or to do different actions, you have to create new grooves.

21:19.384 --> 21:20.946
That does not happen overnight.

21:21.474 --> 21:23.676
That does not happen at the flip of a switch.

21:24.397 --> 21:27.300
Sometimes it doesn't happen over weeks or even months.

21:28.701 --> 21:38.471
The toughest of grooves, that needs to happen sometimes three, four, five years, sometimes longer than that.

21:40.093 --> 21:49.362
When we're talking about a transformed life in its neuroscience kind of way, we're literally talking about putting new grooves in our minds.

21:49.442 --> 21:54.527
And I love that Paul says the transformation of our minds, right?

21:55.508 --> 22:00.132
He doesn't know that neuroscience behind all this, but it does take time.

22:00.172 --> 22:08.480
And I guess what I'm asking from you is patience, patience with yourself to take the time it takes.

22:09.522 --> 22:18.290
But endurance, Paul speaks at length about enduring and being persistent and sticking with it

22:18.850 --> 22:25.299
Because transformation, it doesn't happen by making some kind of commitment this morning and saying, yep, you know what, I'm gonna start working out.

22:26.541 --> 22:30.227
This is something that you have to do day after day after day.

22:30.988 --> 22:35.555
Heck, this is what Paul is talking about when he says becoming a living sacrifice.

22:36.776 --> 22:48.754
The problem with a living sacrifice is that it wants to crawl off the altar, but every single day, you've gotta put it back on there and find your way to new grooves that the sled of your life

22:48.930 --> 22:49.711
is creating.

22:50.312 --> 22:51.754
And yes, it's going to be awkward.

22:52.314 --> 22:53.476
Yes, it's going to be hard.

22:55.178 --> 23:00.445
But if the Bible teaches us anything, it teaches us that's where abundant life lies.

23:01.926 --> 23:06.312
So we are to be transformed by the renewal of our minds.

23:07.253 --> 23:10.497
The goal is not just so we're clear to be better caterpillars.

23:11.358 --> 23:14.162
The goal is butterfly, right?

23:14.658 --> 23:17.944
It's not just strengthening our caterpillar selves.

23:18.385 --> 23:23.794
The ultimate goal is something that is wholly and totally different.

23:25.457 --> 23:27.841
I think this is what the resurrection teaches us as well.

23:28.502 --> 23:34.473
Jesus dies and he is resurrected from the dead and he's similar, but he's different.

23:35.375 --> 23:39.602
He still is able to eat with his friends, but he's also

23:39.682 --> 23:44.529
kind of walking through walls and showing up in different places at different times.

23:45.650 --> 23:52.219
That is a form of transformation that we're not gonna get in this lifetime, just in case you're wondering.

23:53.380 --> 23:58.467
However, we are being called eventually to that butterfly state.

23:59.449 --> 24:09.362
And our job is to allow God to work in and through us as we proceed through this life, transforming us

24:09.442 --> 24:17.394
from glory into glory until eventually we get to glory and we are transformed into that butterfly completely.

24:19.577 --> 24:27.469
One of my favorite theologians is a guy named Thomas Merton and he says the biggest human temptation is to settle for too little.

24:28.331 --> 24:31.115
The biggest human temptation is to settle for too little.

24:31.175 --> 24:35.762
Now if this man were like a corporate executive you might think

24:36.098 --> 24:40.083
Oh, he's talking about, you know, climbing the right corporate ladder or something like that.

24:41.225 --> 24:45.650
The man was a monk living in a small monastery in Louisville, Kentucky.

24:46.171 --> 24:52.739
So he wasn't talking about settling for too little in the terms of how the world would describe too little.

24:54.181 --> 25:04.274
I think what he's talking about is we settle for like the caterpillar larva stage maybe, or the smaller, and he's saying no, no, no, no.

25:04.994 --> 25:06.176
We need to think big.

25:06.977 --> 25:10.062
God wants to do a big thing in your soul.

25:10.783 --> 25:15.129
He wants to change you dramatically from the inside out.

25:15.850 --> 25:18.314
And the question is, will you let him?

25:19.175 --> 25:24.844
Will you dream the biggest dreams possible about what God can do in your life?

25:25.905 --> 25:28.449
Or will you settle for too little?

25:30.532 --> 25:34.418
Final question is, how does all of this work?

25:35.874 --> 25:38.497
And the truth is God.

25:39.898 --> 25:41.400
And I don't know.

25:41.440 --> 25:43.402
Those are my two answers.

25:44.663 --> 25:45.264
God does it.

25:46.064 --> 25:46.985
And I don't fully know.

25:47.566 --> 25:48.427
But I do know this.

25:48.467 --> 25:51.050
It doesn't happen in the blink of an eye.

25:52.211 --> 25:57.456
It takes often years or really even a lifetime of transformation.

25:58.537 --> 26:03.282
So get ready for the long game, the long haul, and the day in,

26:03.362 --> 26:05.705
day out work of transformation.

26:06.846 --> 26:10.150
But I also know that it's intentional and it's directional.

26:10.770 --> 26:12.412
That we're pointing toward somewhere.

26:12.833 --> 26:14.334
We're aiming at a goal.

26:14.575 --> 26:19.460
And as I told the kids, the goal is nothing less than becoming like the person of Jesus.

26:20.241 --> 26:21.082
We have a model.

26:21.623 --> 26:22.824
We have someone to look at.

26:23.365 --> 26:25.948
And we have someone to model our lives after.

26:28.330 --> 26:28.971
How do we do it?

26:29.612 --> 26:31.474
I do think it involves sacrifice.

26:31.938 --> 26:33.760
We are living sacrifices.

26:34.582 --> 26:42.252
Our day in and our day out are intended to be sacrificed to the one who sacrificed his life for us.

26:43.393 --> 26:45.396
And I believe that we are what we do.

26:46.658 --> 26:50.323
Your mind is not transformed by thinking about it.

26:51.164 --> 26:54.548
Your mind is transformed by doing something about it.

26:55.730 --> 26:57.652
By actually changing your actions.

26:58.714 --> 27:00.316
And yes, you will fail.

27:01.137 --> 27:01.938
We all do.

27:02.978 --> 27:05.821
but you stay at it and you keep going.

27:07.602 --> 27:12.447
If you want the transformed mind, it starts with living the life of service to God.

27:13.268 --> 27:21.636
Through the repetition of this kind of life, your brain will literally be rewired, but it will take the time that it takes.

27:22.297 --> 27:26.921
And so if you want to be a person of faith, we'll live like a person of faith.

27:27.542 --> 27:32.146
And if you want to be a person of joy, we'll then live like a person of joy.

27:32.226 --> 27:52.052
And if you want your mind transformed into the mind of Christ, as Paul tells us elsewhere, well, then the best thing you can do is to live as Christ lived, to serve others first, to love the world, to die to self, and above all, to submit your will to the will of the Father.

27:54.655 --> 27:58.580
Tonight continues the service we are starting right now.

27:59.521 --> 28:00.082
Tonight

28:00.290 --> 28:08.039
You might think of as our first night in the gym together as we begin this training course.

28:09.721 --> 28:15.487
And if we are going to live transformed lives, it is always going to start with prayer.

28:15.527 --> 28:19.031
It is always going to start with seeking God.

28:22.315 --> 28:25.038
Tonight is a week of worship and prayer.

28:25.098 --> 28:28.242
And my hope is that you come ready

28:28.386 --> 28:37.505
to put new sled tracks in the ground, to maybe hop out of some of the old ones that you've been in, and to regroup your mind.

28:38.707 --> 28:45.922
We are going to spend five nights in the presence of God, putting the old behind us, and striving toward the new.

28:47.626 --> 28:49.650
It is a continuation of this service.

28:50.274 --> 28:52.818
We intentionally did not serve communion.

28:53.399 --> 28:54.941
Actually, I kind of apologize for it.

28:55.181 --> 28:59.207
We probably could have served it this morning and then again this evening.

28:59.988 --> 29:04.475
But I do want to serve communion this evening and we will gather together and we will do so.

29:05.116 --> 29:20.178
And the reason in my mind that is important that we do so this evening is because we will have spent time together praising God, worshiping, contemplating, praying, interceding for one another and confessing.

29:20.834 --> 29:28.302
And then when we take communion, we will do so because we want to live out what Paul says in Romans 12 here.

29:29.343 --> 29:39.895
We are offering our lives as a living sacrifice because of the mercies of God, because Christ offered his life for us.

29:40.655 --> 29:50.386
And so as we take communion, we are reminded of where all this started, which is essentially Romans 1 through 11, that God loves us.

29:51.202 --> 30:00.819
that He's for us, that He's coming after us, that His mercies are new every day, that He has sent His Son, Jesus Christ, to die for us.

30:01.701 --> 30:13.603
And our response, the overflow of our heart to that invitation is to say, yes, I give you my life, I entrust myself to your ways.

30:14.785 --> 30:15.506
Let us pray together.

30:20.962 --> 30:22.885
Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

30:23.706 --> 30:33.100
We need you this morning and we will need you this afternoon and this evening and tonight and tomorrow and again and again and again.

30:37.667 --> 30:42.414
God, our gathering is a beautiful thing.

30:43.896 --> 30:47.922
You have told us to gather regularly and to not give that up.

30:48.610 --> 30:55.559
because there is something in the gathering that is important in the transformation process.

30:55.579 --> 30:57.722
We encourage one another.

30:57.742 --> 31:00.907
We spur one another on to your ways.

31:02.028 --> 31:04.371
We teach one another.

31:04.391 --> 31:07.075
We're inspired by one another's stories.

31:08.497 --> 31:18.130
But God, then we have the messy work of the lived life of a Monday and of a Tuesday, Wednesday, classes, school,

31:18.562 --> 31:32.797
We pray that it be a year of transformation.

31:32.817 --> 31:37.923
There's some hard decisions.

31:37.963 --> 31:48.434
There's some new ruts that need to be created and some old ruts that need to get out.

31:50.498 --> 32:00.434
That would give you praise.

